titleproper.value:
Guide to the Candida Scott Piel Papers and AmFAR Collection
                    <lb/>1969-2003 (Bulk 1981-2003)
                    <lb/>
                    <num>MSS 142</num>

author.value: Finding aid prepared by Fales Library, 2003.

creation.value:
This finding aid was produced using the Archivists' Toolkit
                <date>2014-06-10T16:00-0400</date>

unittitle.value: Candida Scott Piel Papers and AmFAR Collection

extent.value: (2 document cases, 2 flat boxes, 1 objects box)

abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: The Candida Scott Piel Papers and AmFAR Collection contains administrative files, clippings, and ephemera related to Candida Scott Piel and her involvement with the Foundation for AIDS Research (AmFAR).

p.value: Audiovisual materials have not been preserved and may not be available to researchers.

Published citations should take the following form: 
                <lb/>
                <lb/>Identification of item, date (if known); Candida Scott Piel Papers and AmFAR Collection; MSS 142; box number; folder number; New York University Libraries.

Candida Scott Piel worked with the Foundation for AIDS Research (AmFAR) and other Gay and Lesbian Advocates' Groups throughout the 1980s and 1990s. Her work included involvement with numerous outreach events, such as the annual New York City Gay Pride Celebration.

The Candida Scott Piel Papers and AmFAR Collection contains administrative files, clippings, and ephemera related to Candida Scott Piel's involvement with the Foundation for AIDS Research (AmFAR) and other AIDS and LGBT outreach initiatives. The materials have been arranged into three series:
                <lb/>
                <lb/>
                <emph render="bold">Series I: Event Materials</emph> contains items related to specific events which Candida Scott Piel attended, or with which she was involved, including film festivals, LGBT rights events, and political meetings.
                <lb/>
                <lb/>
                <emph render="bold">Series II: Subject Files</emph> contains clippings and research files unrelated to specific events.
                <lb/>
                <lb/>
                <emph render="bold">Series III: Ephemera</emph> contains primarily promotional items such as buttons and t-shirts, related to groups or events.
